Durban - Police are still searching for the suspect who shot an off-duty metro policewoman on Saturday night in Verulam. According to KZN police spokesperson, Colonel Thembeka Mbele, the  40-year-old woman was seated inside her stationary vehicle in Champion Crescent at around 10:15pm when an unknown man opened fire on her. She said the wounded woman was rushed to a hospital for medical attention. The suspect supposedly fled the crime scene in a Hyundai. "A case of attempted murder was opened at Verulam police station for investigation." Mbele said no one had been arrested. According to Prem Balram, director of Reaction Unit SA, the victim was driving a VW Golf 7 when an unknown gunman opened fire on her vehicle as she approached a stop street in Verulam. "The Metro Police officer was struck multiple times on her body and head. She was rushed to hospital privately. At least 10 spent cartridges were found at the scene," said Balram. Daily News